laboratory_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated to 8 mm and fluid filled with a hyperenhancing wall consistent with appendicitis. There is a proximal obstructing appendicolith. No evidence of perforation or abscess formation. A small amount of free fluid layering dependently within the pelvis. Kidneys enhance and excrete contrast symmetrically without hydronephrosis. Small sub-cm hypodense lesion in the upper pole of the right kidney, likely a cyst.
